      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>While no date is provided within the text, the inscription has been dated to the early fifth century CE based on other factors. The tombstone is one of about 700 discovered in Byzantine Zoora. The majority of the Greek tombstones from this location have been identified as Christian. The tombstone has an irregular form, and is broken in the lower left corner. The text is engraved. A cross-rho is engraved beneath the text. This cross-rho is flanked by an alpha and an omega.</p>
         </div>
